## {{ rule.title }}

[26 U.S.C. § 3101(b)(2)](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section3101) imposes a **0.9 % Additional Medicare Tax** on Medicare-taxable wages above the filing-status threshold; [§ 1401(b)(2)](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1401) imposes the same 0.9 % on SE-taxable earnings. The threshold is **shared** across the two bases (single threshold across wages + SE) and is statutory (not inflation-indexed):

- $200,000 — Single (and Head of Household)
- $250,000 — Married Filing Jointly
- $125,000 — Married Filing Separately

[Form 8959](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-8959) implements the combined wage/SE arithmetic. The result lands on Schedule 2 line 11.

